message: It should be outside if you left without getting it.
Hold the banana and then press down on your d-pad to switch to long range drop.
Use bananas as bait and you can one-shot sneakstrike them while they're ~~running~~ prancing up to it. I used a torch to kill them for fun.
When does that happen?
There both combat-related abilities so I wouldn't say they're must-haves.
You can disable it? How?

The regular ones don't really do anything but the colored ones are used to upgrade armor later on and also have specific qualities. For example, red has fire so you can use it to light a campifire or something. White has power of ice. Yellow has the power of electricity. You can turn regular blue jelly into the other ones by applying that element to them. So if you put some jelly on a campfire, it'll turn into red. If you drop some into freezing water or a cold environment it'll turn to white.
The jagged rocks in the water means you have to throw a rock into the center. There's usually a pile of rocks nearby so you have several tries.
That's where Kilton sets up shop at night.
If you're looking for a full set, the coliseum will have enemies that have all 3 elements in all 3 weapon types if you're far enough into the game
14 hearts should be plenty as long as you have decent armor. You probably won't be one-shot by anything if you have a set of armor that's at least upgraded twice.
Right where you teleport out
